---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';

/*
  Dated research note — frozen to Nebius Group's ~$775M senior secured debt
  facility, announced by company release 2026-07-17 (furnished as Exhibit 99.1
  to a Form 6-K the same day). Research notes are dated, not updated in place;
  the living surface is /credit (instrument ledger). Every figure traces to a
  Nebius primary source only:
    - Facility: company release "Nebius raises $775 million in first secured
      debt financing" (2026-07-17) = Form 6-K EX-99.1, acc 0001104659-26-084452.
    - Convertibles: Form 6-K, March 2026, acc 0001104659-26-029863.
  This page must not import the live datasets.
*/
const AS_OF = '2026-07-20';
const RELEASE_URL = 'https://nebius.com/newsroom/nebius-raises-775-million-in-first-secured-debt-financing-to-accelerate-global-buildout';
---
<Base
  title="Nebius's First Secured Debt: A $775M GPU-Backed Facility · CCIR Research"
  description="In July 2026, Nebius entered its first senior secured debt facility, ~$775M — its first secured debt, after a debt history made up entirely of convertible notes. The facility, its bank syndicate, and the change of instrument."
  ogImage="/og/nebius-first-secured-debt.png"
  article={{ published: '2026-07-20' }}
>
  <section class="wrap top">
    <header class="page-head">
      <div class="kicker">Research · {AS_OF} · new issuance</div>
      <h1>Nebius's First Secured Debt: A $775M GPU-Backed Facility</h1>
      <p class="standfirst">
        On July 17, 2026, Nebius Group announced it had entered into its first
        senior secured debt facility, for approximately $775 million — its
        first secured debt, after a debt history made up entirely of
        convertible notes. This note records the facility and the change of
        instrument.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="sec">
      <h2><span class="n">01</span> The Facility</h2>
      <p>
        The facility is a senior secured debt facility of approximately
        $775 million, priced at SOFR plus 2.50% and maturing October 31, 2030.
        Nebius describes it as senior secured debt backed by deployed GPU
        infrastructure and the contracted cash flows from an agreement with an
        investment-grade customer; together with those cash flows, the facility
        is stated to cover more than 100% of the capital expenditure required
        to deploy the underlying GPU infrastructure.
      </p>
      <p>
        The transaction was significantly oversubscribed. MUFG acted as
        structuring agent, sole bookrunner and underwriter; MUFG, ABN AMRO,
        Bank of America, Deutsche Bank and HSBC as mandated lead arrangers;
        Citi, Crédit Agricole CIB, ING and Morgan Stanley as senior lead
        arrangers, with Goldman Sachs also participating in the syndicate.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="sec">
      <h2><span class="n">02</span> The Change of Instrument</h2>
      <p>
        It is the first secured debt in the company's history. Nebius's
        borrowings to date had been convertibles — senior unsecured notes
        carrying an equity conversion option, a low coupon, a bullet maturity,
        and light covenants, held by equity-linked investors with nothing
        pledged. As recently as March 2026 the company priced $4.0 billion of
        convertible senior notes in two series.
      </p>
      <p>
        The facility is a different instrument with a different lender base: a
        first-lien claim held by a commercial-bank syndicate, with scheduled
        terms running to 2030. The move is from convertible notes to secured
        bank debt — the first time Nebius has funded on that basis.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="sec">
      <h2><span class="n">03</span> The Record</h2>
      <p>
        We record every GPU-backed facility we can trace to a primary
        document in the <a href="/credit">compute credit tracker</a>, and this
        facility is entered there. Derived series — spread at signing and
        lender-filed marks — are on the <a href="/credit/series">credit
        reference series</a> page.
      </p>
      <p class="footnote">
        Sources: Nebius Group N.V., <a href={RELEASE_URL}>"Nebius raises
        $775 million in first secured debt financing"</a> (company release,
        July 17, 2026), furnished as Exhibit 99.1 to Form 6-K (SEC accession
        0001104659-26-084452). Convertible-note figures: Nebius Group N.V.,
        Form 6-K, March 2026 — pricing of $4.0 billion of convertible senior
        notes ($2.25 billion 1.250% due 2031; $1.75 billion 2.625% due 2033),
        SEC accession 0001104659-26-029863.
      </p>
    </section>
  </section>

  <style>
    .top { padding-top: 32px; }
    .page-head { max-width: 82ch; margin-bottom: 10px; }
    .page-head h1 {
      font-family: var(--font-display);
      font-size: var(--fs-hero);
      line-height: var(--lh-display);
      font-weight: var(--weight-display);
      margin: 6px 0 14px;
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    }
    .sec { margin: 28px 0; max-width: 80ch; }
    .sec h2 {
      font-family: var(--font-display);
      font-size: var(--fs-xl);
      margin: 0 0 12px;
      display: flex;
      align-items: baseline;
      gap: 12px;
    }
    .sec .n { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--fs-sm); color: var(--accent); font-weight: var(--weight-strong); }
    .sec p { font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: var(--fs-md); color: var(--ink); line-height: 1.65; margin: 0 0 13px; }
    .footnote {
      font-size: var(--fs-sm);
      color: var(--ink-faint);
      border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
      padding-top: 8px;
      max-width: 74ch;
    }
    .footnote a { color: var(--accent); }
  </style>
</Base>
